body:
The first one is easy:

``` diff
diff --git a/OpenRA.Editor/Surface.cs b/OpenRA.Editor/Surface.cs
index 3def5aa..93f6c1b 100644
--- a/OpenRA.Editor/Surface.cs
+++ b/OpenRA.Editor/Surface.cs
@@ -391,7 +391,7 @@ void DrawActorBorder(SGraphics g, CPos p, ActorTemplate t)
                ColorPalette GetPaletteForPlayerInner(string name)
                {
                        var pr = new MapPlayers(Map.PlayerDefinitions).Players[name];
-                       var pcpi = Program.Rules.Actors["player"].Traits.Get<PlayerColorPaletteInfo>();
+                       var pcpi = Program.Rules.Actors["world"].Traits.Get<PlayerColorPaletteInfo>();
                        var remap = new PlayerColorRemap(pcpi.RemapIndex, pr.Color, pcpi.Ramp);
                        return new ImmutablePalette(PlayerPalette, remap).AsSystemPalette();
                }
```

No idea about the second one.

Edit:
ok, so it's crashing with this combination of parameters:

```
U/V: 0, 16; i: 0, j: 2; UI/VJ: 0, 130
```

which of course crashes since the cell layer ends at index 129. (128 + 1 cell border on each side, starting at 0). Still no idea how to change the calculations in `RenderChunk` to avoid that.

well, the patch below makes the crash go away, but produces artifacts in the rendering outside the map.

``` diff
diff --git a/OpenRA.Editor/Surface.cs b/OpenRA.Editor/Surface.cs
index 3def5aa..58779ff 100644
--- a/OpenRA.Editor/Surface.cs
+++ b/OpenRA.Editor/Surface.cs
@@ -278,6 +278,9 @@ Bitmap RenderChunk(int u, int v)
                                                var ui = u * ChunkSize + i;
                                                var vj = v * ChunkSize + j;
                                                var uv = new MPos(ui, vj);
+                                               if (!Map.Contains(uv))
+                                                       continue;
+
                                                var tr = Map.MapTiles.Value[uv];
                                                var tile = TileSetRenderer.Data(tr.Type);
                                                if (tile == null)
```

